Bug.WithStack:
This is related to bug #88640 and bug bug #77566. Eclipse 3.2 starts use new API (just great!), but org.eclipse.jdt.internal.junit.launcher.JUnitBaseLaunchConfiguration.java calls
String[] envp = DebugPlugin.getDefault().getLaunchManager().getEnvironment(configuration);
instead of String[] envp = this.getEnvironment(configuration);
It makes impossible to change environment in derived classes. I suggest to implement "getEnvironment" method in JUnitBaseLaunchConfiguration, which will return result of DebugPlugin.getDefault().getLaunchManager().getEnvironment(configuration) call.
Regards, Vladimir Kondratyev fixed > 20051117.
Note that unless JUnitBaseLaunchConfiguration is API, you are on thin ice when subtyping this class. Verifying... Verified in I20051213-0010.

