Created attachment 30142
stack trace from .log file
Created attachment 30984
Simpler testcase

In this testcase both the shell and the composite share the same method, with a button inside the composite. Moving the button from the composite to the shell creates the same problem.
When reparenting a SWT child the order its performed is:
1. Remove from old-parent 'controls'
2. Set an orphan/transiet parent in 'allocation'
3. Set the new-parent 'allocation'
4. Add to new-parent 'controls'

What was broken in codegen was step 3, where an 'allocation' is set without the child being in the 'controls'. Due to this codegen generates a source of null which throws an NPE. 
As a fix, now codegen realizes the null content and removes the expression from the code. This is advantageous as when the child is later added into the 'controls' of the parent, the code is re-generated at the correct index/offset and magically all other expressions move behind the contructor.

Releasing fixes in SWTConstructorDecoderHelper.java and CodeExpressionRef.java.
Closing

