PI code that reproduces the problem

Here is testcase written with OS calls only that shows the problem.
I was not able to reproduce the problem in Eclipse following the steps of bug#134515 or bug#132739.

Do these steps reproduce the problem all the time for you?
(In reply to comment #7)
> I was not able to reproduce the problem in Eclipse following the steps of
> bug#134515 or bug#132739.
> 
> Do these steps reproduce the problem all the time for you?

Yes, although my steps weren't clear enough, here is another try:

1. open the plugin.xml editor
2. Make sure there is something under the editor, like the console view
3. Go to the build tab
4. Arrange the views and editor so that there are scroll bars present on both
the editor and the binary build list
5. Scroll the editor so that the binary build list is partially obscured by the view under the editor
6. Scroll the binary build list

Without step 5 you will not see the problem.
Actually I've just seen that its more tricky, you also need to make sure that the editor scroll bar isn't at the top, moving it about half way down does it.
